blog.title: Catelyn Stark was mean to the godswood

summary: In season 1, Daenerys saw Drogo as her only source of power and security in patriarchal society and was desperate to keep it, to...
body: In season 1, Daenerys saw Drogo as her only source of power and security in patriarchal society and was desperate to keep it, to the point where she expected Mirri Maz Duur, a woman enslaved and abused by Dothraki, to help her. In season 6, Daenerys returns to the beginning, but this time she bonds with Ornela, another enslaved and abused Lhazareen woman, and instead of upholding the patriarchy, she fucking burns it to the ground. And if this isn’t some epic character growth, I don’t know what it is.
